Module net.automatalib.common.util
Package net.automatalib.common.util.array

Class ArrayStorage<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<T>
        • net.automatalib.common.util.array.ArrayStorage<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of stored elements
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, List<T>, RandomAccess
    public final class ArrayStorage<T>
extends AbstractList<T>
implements RandomAccess
    A type-safe wrapper around a simple Object[] array. This class is mainly useful when in need for heavily generic index-based data storage. While it is compatible with Lists, it does not support dynamic growth but explicit memory allocation. As a result, elements can be set at non-contiguous positions.

    • Method Detail

      • ensureCapacity

        public boolean ensureCapacity​(int minCapacity)
        Ensures that the storage container can store at least the given amount of elements. Note that the implementation may allocate more memory (to speed up subsequent increments) but elements can only ever be accessed until the requested position.
        Parameters:
        minCapacity - the minimum capacity required
        Returns:
        true if the internal storage was re-allocated, false otherwise
